  "instructions": [
    "Heat the olive oil in a large skillet over medium heat.",
    "Add the minced garlic and sauté for 3-4 minutes until fragrant.",
    "Add the shredded cacao pods and grated ginger, and sauté for 2-3 minutes.",
    "Add the lemon juice, salt, black pepper, and citrus zest, and stir to combine.",
    "Add the coconut milk and water, and stir to combine.",
    "Bring the mixture to a simmer and cook for 5-7 minutes until the sauce has thickened.",
    "Reduce the heat to low and let the sauce simmer for 5-7 minutes.",
    "Taste and adjust the seasoning as needed.",
    "Serve the Citrusy Energizing Kenyan Garlic Tagine hot, garnished with additional citrus zest if desired."
